        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 2:00PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Richmond, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Richmond, Spears, Blue Grass, Redhouse, Baldwin, Valley View, Cuzick,
Hillcrest, Newby, and Million.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
